{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Improve statutory paternity leave in the UK to better support families.",
        "additional_details": "We think the current statutory provisions for paternity leave are insufficient in length and pay, failing to adequately support new fathers and partners during the critical early weeks of a child\u2019s life. We think this contributes to inequality in shared parenting responsibilities and undermines family wellbeing.",
        "background": "1. Extend statutory paternity leave to a minimum of six weeks.\r\n2. Increase statutory paternity pay to full income replacement.\r\n3. Make it a legal requirement for employers to offer flexible arrangements to employees taking paternity leave (e.g. taking in chunks)\r\n",
